\begin{document}
}{}$Q_{AT2}^*(T)$\end{document} for 200 bp windows along the genomes of 10 representative species, from strong to weak genome-wide periodicity. Each window is assigned to a period Tsig, which achieves the smallest P-value in permutation tests (Supporting Methods). In agreement with a previous windowed scan (9), the distribution of windows with period Tsig (Supplementary Figure S8A–J) reveals an additional peak at ∼10 bp in four Cyanothece sp. and Synechocystis sp. PCC 6803. An additional averaging of AT2 spectra \documentclass[12pt]{minimal}
